CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 10, 1955, pg. 4 reads: "Protest Rezoning - City Council heard arguments, pro and con, Tuesday, concerning the proposed ordinance to change from Class "B" to "A" property bounded by Chalfont Street, Delmont Avenue, Bolivar Way and Gearing Avenue, in the Eighteenth Ward (Beltzhoover), that wouldn't permit the establishment of a funeral home at 616 Delmont Avenue...lower center, Atty. W.D. Sutton, representing the protesting faction, outside Council chambers, following the hearing...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Atty. W.D. Sutton, standing outside Council chambers with group of men and women, after Beltzhoover re-zoning hearing, in City County Building
